"""Capacity Chronicles

std::vector tracks two different numbers -- size() (how many elements are actually stored) and capacity() (how much room is currently reserved before a reallocation is needed) -- and mixing them up is one of the most common std::vector misunderstandings. Every snippet here pins capacity with reserve() (since the growth factor itself is implementation-defined and never guaranteed by the standard) and prints only size()/capacity()/element-value facts that are fully standard-guaranteed, so every predicted output is deterministic on any conforming compiler.
"""
